What would otherwise have been a series of excellent but disconnected puzzles becomes something deeper.

456
00:30:02,414 --> 00:30:11,638
As the player completes abstract tasks after abstract tasks, they begin to wonder who they are, what their role is in this world, and whether they have any power over it.

457
00:30:11,638 --> 00:30:14,700
The team created a story of free will.

458
00:30:15,855 --> 00:30:19,837
The cube, like the player, is innocent, trapped in this bizarre environment.

459
00:30:19,837 --> 00:30:22,639
And we're used to being bossed around by Gladys.

460
00:30:22,639 --> 00:30:26,321
We now want to reject what we're being told.

461
00:30:26,321 --> 00:30:28,642
So when we reach the end, when we reach the incinerator,

462
00:30:28,642 --> 00:30:31,423
we're identifying with the cube.

463
00:30:31,423 --> 00:30:33,825
The companion cube in this world is the same as the player.

464
00:30:34,752 --> 00:30:37,974
And this pushes the game from abstract mechanics

465
00:30:37,974 --> 00:30:40,875
through representation and into simulation,

466
00:30:40,875 --> 00:30:45,977
the result being people developed feelings for a cube.

467
00:30:45,977 --> 00:30:49,218
Can a computer make you cry?

468
00:30:49,218 --> 00:30:49,758
Yes, it can.

469
00:30:51,161 --> 00:30:57,262
So to sum up, when you're examining emotion in games, there are four main things that are useful to think about.

470
00:30:57,262 --> 00:31:01,243
Who is feeling the emotion in your game? Simulation, representation, abstraction.

471
00:31:01,243 --> 00:31:05,184
What emotion is the player supposed to feel? Theme, genre.

472
00:31:05,184 --> 00:31:08,885
How do we communicate emotion in a game? Tell, show, do.

473
00:31:08,885 --> 00:31:11,406
And why does the player feel emotion?

474
00:31:12,393 --> 00:31:17,738
context, structure. By looking at emotions as interactive, as something to interpret,

475
00:31:17,738 --> 00:31:23,504
you can go forth and help the player to fall in love, cry, hope, dream and explore another

476
00:31:23,504 --> 00:31:30,571
thousand different emotions, all while keeping them in the game. Good luck. Thank you very much

477
00:31:30,571 --> 00:31:36,357
for coming along today. I hope that's very useful for you. Have fun and be emotional out there.

